Etymology
. From the Greek στυραξ (= 
styrax
), meaning "spine at the butt end of a spear" (
Brown, 1954
), and ουρα (= 
oura
) meaning tail, a suffix commonly used since 
Müller & Henle (1837)
for whiptailed stingrays—in reference to its greatly elongated caudal stings. Gender feminine.
